partment in 1942  Under the program  Army enlisted men were sent to various colleges and universities to take coursework in engineering and allied subjects  The first ASTP students arrived at VMI on May 7  1943  the program ended on April 27  1946  with a total of 2  148 having taken part in the Institute s ASTP courses  These  Army students  were typically stationed at VMI for a few weeks or months and then were sent overseas or for additional training elswhere  They were not enrolled as VMI cadets and are not carried on the rolls as VMI alumni  However  shortly after the war Institute officials compiled a complete roster of the men who trained at VMI  which is available below  View selected documents from the VMI Archives ASTP Roster   Course Description  A list of all men who trained at VMI  May 1943 April 1946 VMI Yearbook  ASTP Section  1944  Excerpt   Cadet Life during World War II From an essay by James M  Morgan  Jr  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 